WEBVTT

00:06.173 --> 00:07.925
[Alex] Okay. Let's go back.

00:07.925 --> 00:10.177
What happened before then?

00:10.177 --> 00:12.012
[Kaya] Well, I come out
of the bathroom stall,

00:12.012 --> 00:14.014
and he's standing there.

00:14.014 --> 00:17.059
He started crying a little,

00:17.059 --> 00:19.478
and then he got down
on the floor

00:19.478 --> 00:22.648
and started trying
to sniff me.

00:22.648 --> 00:23.691
[pen scratching on paper]

00:23.691 --> 00:25.735
Sort of like a dog.

00:27.903 --> 00:30.906
Well, it is good thing that
your company brought me in,

00:30.906 --> 00:32.575
because that does say

00:32.575 --> 00:35.035
that they wanna get
to the bottom of this.

00:35.035 --> 00:37.288
Did you talk to anyone else
about it?

00:37.288 --> 00:40.040
A friend or, um, family member?

00:40.040 --> 00:41.917
No, I just...

00:41.917 --> 00:44.295
I just wanted things
to go back to normal.

00:44.295 --> 00:45.796
I didn't even wanna
think about it.

00:46.505 --> 00:47.548
I understand.

00:50.426 --> 00:52.261
So it's just my word
against his?

00:52.261 --> 00:54.889
That happens a lot
in cases like this.

00:54.889 --> 00:56.807
It does make things
very difficult.

01:04.815 --> 01:05.941
No.

01:05.941 --> 01:07.276
Fuck it.

01:07.276 --> 01:08.360
What he did is not okay.

01:08.360 --> 01:09.528
He needs to be stopped.

01:10.529 --> 01:11.697
Right?

01:13.324 --> 01:14.325
Right.

01:16.118 --> 01:17.119
Yeah.

01:18.245 --> 01:19.622
That's always the hope.

01:19.622 --> 01:21.415
[pen scratching on paper]

01:21.415 --> 01:22.875
What do you mean?

01:25.252 --> 01:26.253
[exhales heavily]

01:27.797 --> 01:28.839
Did...

01:28.839 --> 01:30.800
[pen continues scratching]

01:30.800 --> 01:32.510
It happened to you too,
didn't it?

01:35.179 --> 01:38.641
[solemn orchestral music]

01:38.641 --> 01:39.683
[recorder beeps off]

01:41.644 --> 01:44.271
♪ ♪

01:44.271 --> 01:45.898
[exhales deeply]

01:45.898 --> 01:48.192
♪ ♪

01:48.192 --> 01:49.652
It was years ago.

01:49.652 --> 01:51.654
And I wanted to ruin him.

01:51.654 --> 01:53.405
I wanted to destroy him.

01:53.405 --> 01:55.282
So what did you do?

01:55.282 --> 01:57.201
[Alex] I did what
all my friends told me to do,

01:57.201 --> 01:58.536
what I'm here to help you do.

02:00.162 --> 02:01.205
I filed a claim.

02:02.456 --> 02:03.874
[Kaya] And what happened?

02:03.874 --> 02:05.042
They picked it apart.

02:05.668 --> 02:08.379
They said I was liar,
that I wanted money.

02:09.255 --> 02:10.673
[inhales sharply] In the end,

02:10.673 --> 02:12.216
I got this ridiculous
little settlement

02:12.216 --> 02:14.176
and he got
six weeks paid leave.

02:14.176 --> 02:15.886
When he came back,
he and his friends,

02:15.886 --> 02:17.763
they went out to lunch
to celebrate.

02:17.763 --> 02:19.723
Guess who had to make
the reservation.

02:19.723 --> 02:21.392
Oh, my God.

02:21.392 --> 02:23.310
One day, I just asked myself,

02:23.310 --> 02:24.687
"Why am I doing this?"

02:25.604 --> 02:26.772
And you quit?

02:27.648 --> 02:28.899
I quit.

02:28.899 --> 02:35.489
♪ ♪

02:35.489 --> 02:36.615
I quit...

02:37.449 --> 02:38.742
[exhales heavily]

02:39.660 --> 02:42.705
...and I booked
a one-way ticket to India...

02:42.705 --> 02:43.831
and I got my life back.

02:43.831 --> 02:48.627
♪ ♪

02:48.627 --> 02:49.879
Listen to me.

02:51.171 --> 02:53.215
You need to do
what you think is right.

02:55.175 --> 02:57.970
But you must protect yourself,

02:57.970 --> 02:59.388
because nobody else will.

02:59.388 --> 03:06.395
♪ ♪

03:06.395 --> 03:09.398
[orchestral music
darkening slowly]

03:09.398 --> 03:16.071
♪ ♪

03:16.071 --> 03:19.074
[dark music]

03:19.074 --> 03:26.081
♪ ♪

03:33.422 --> 03:34.924
- [elevator bell dings]
- [music stops]

03:43.223 --> 03:46.226
[upbeat pop music]

03:46.226 --> 03:48.395
[Alex] It's done.
She's leaving the company.

03:48.395 --> 03:50.272
[Bob] She's letting
the whole thing go?

03:50.272 --> 03:52.358
- You sure?
- Yep, the whole thing.

03:52.358 --> 03:54.568
Your crisis has been managed.

03:54.568 --> 03:56.028
Just look out for my invoice.

03:56.028 --> 03:57.696
[Bob] Alex, that's amazing.

03:57.696 --> 03:59.365
Oh, and Bob...

03:59.365 --> 04:01.408
[Bob] Yeah?
- You're not a dog, Bob.

04:01.408 --> 04:02.910
You're a man.
Quit sniffing.

04:02.910 --> 04:03.953
[Bob] It wasn't exactly...

04:03.953 --> 04:05.454
[cell phone beeps off]

04:05.454 --> 04:07.915
[pop music playing
over speakers]

04:07.915 --> 04:09.458
♪ ♪

04:09.458 --> 04:10.876
[giggles]

04:10.876 --> 04:16.757
♪ ♪

04:16.757 --> 04:19.093
[gentle music]

04:19.093 --> 04:21.428
[phone line trills]

04:21.428 --> 04:22.596
[Temple] Hey.

04:22.596 --> 04:23.472
[Alex] Hi.

04:24.098 --> 04:25.516
Guess what I'm doing.

04:25.516 --> 04:26.350
What?

04:27.226 --> 04:29.603
I'm shopping for the cat...
in bulk.

04:29.603 --> 04:31.021
What got into you?
You hate the cat.

04:31.647 --> 04:33.607
Why is there an echo?
Are you in the bathroom?

04:34.358 --> 04:35.317
Maybe.

04:35.943 --> 04:37.152
What happened?

04:37.319 --> 04:38.862
[sniffles]
It's not even worth it.

04:38.862 --> 04:40.364
- Temple.
- What?

04:40.406 --> 04:42.408
It's nothing you haven't heard
a million times.

04:43.158 --> 04:44.451
Colin's bullshit.

04:45.244 --> 04:47.037
[Alex] I don't know why
you keep putting up this.

04:47.037 --> 04:48.789
You have, like,
a million ideas.

04:48.789 --> 04:51.083
Let's pick one
and make that happen.

04:51.083 --> 04:52.543
I'm not gonna do that.

04:52.543 --> 04:53.627
I just...

04:53.627 --> 04:55.087
[breathes deeply]

04:55.087 --> 04:56.672
I just wanna matter here.

04:56.672 --> 04:58.465
♪ ♪

04:58.465 --> 04:59.925
I'm just having a bad day.

04:59.925 --> 05:01.844
♪ ♪

05:01.844 --> 05:03.387
- All right.
[Temple] I gotta go.

05:04.304 --> 05:05.764
[car beeps]

05:05.764 --> 05:07.182
[Alex] Chin up, okay?

05:07.182 --> 05:08.767
Everything's gonna be fine.

05:08.767 --> 05:09.893
[Temple] I love you.

05:09.893 --> 05:12.187
♪ ♪

05:12.187 --> 05:14.815
[Ron] I don't know.
Subways, billboards.

05:14.815 --> 05:15.774
Wherever.

05:15.774 --> 05:16.942
[Wendy] But this?

05:16.942 --> 05:18.027
[Ron] Look, it's happening.

05:18.027 --> 05:19.945
It's done, all right?

05:19.945 --> 05:20.779
[scoffs]

05:20.863 --> 05:22.156
AT and T, what's up?

05:23.657 --> 05:24.825
What?

05:24.825 --> 05:27.077
AT and T. Audrey Temple.

05:27.077 --> 05:28.662
AT...what's your middle name
again?

05:28.662 --> 05:30.122
I don't have one.

05:30.122 --> 05:31.582
- Ah, that's weird.
- Okay, Ron.

05:31.582 --> 05:32.541
Don't torture her.

05:32.541 --> 05:33.709
[Ron] Okay. Look.

05:33.792 --> 05:35.502
Honest opinion.
Don't hold back.

05:35.502 --> 05:36.754
What do you think?

05:37.671 --> 05:38.505
I like it.

05:39.923 --> 05:43.427
But it doesn't...really say
what the roller does, though.

05:44.178 --> 05:45.596
- Ha.
- [stammers wordlessly]

05:45.596 --> 05:47.723
Yes, it does.
It says right here.

05:48.348 --> 05:49.600
[starts, stops]

05:49.600 --> 05:51.018
Get over what, though?

05:51.018 --> 05:53.520
Anxiety, stress, everything.

05:53.520 --> 05:55.189
Just...

05:55.189 --> 05:56.690
it's a teaser, okay?

05:56.690 --> 05:58.692
This broke.
Can you...

05:58.692 --> 06:00.986
[murmuring inaudibly]
...but does it make sense?

06:00.986 --> 06:02.529
Ron,

06:02.529 --> 06:03.864
that is fucking genius.

06:03.864 --> 06:05.074
How did you come up with that?

06:05.074 --> 06:06.825
Thank you.

06:06.825 --> 06:08.077
I was in the shower,
actually, and I was thinking...

06:08.077 --> 06:09.620
[sighs]

06:09.620 --> 06:11.246
[Ron] ..."What does
a roller help you do?"

06:11.246 --> 06:13.123
[Lane] "Get over it."
- Those fucking guys.

06:13.123 --> 06:14.249
[laughs]

06:14.249 --> 06:15.334
It's fine.

06:16.418 --> 06:18.629
Actually, are you heading
into the roller meeting?

06:18.712 --> 06:20.047
Yeah.
What's up?

06:20.047 --> 06:21.548
Do you think I could sit in?

06:21.548 --> 06:22.466
[phone ringing distantly]

06:22.466 --> 06:23.425
Oh, um...

06:23.425 --> 06:24.593
I really think

06:24.593 --> 06:26.011
that there's untapped potential

06:26.011 --> 06:27.262
in the workplace channel.

06:28.555 --> 06:31.016
Imagine you're having
a bad day at work

06:31.016 --> 06:32.976
and you go into the supply area
and...

06:32.976 --> 06:35.562
Oh,
I love how proactive you are.

06:36.105 --> 06:37.314
I put together
some numbers...

06:37.314 --> 06:39.108
[Wendy] Yeah. Nice.
- And...

06:39.108 --> 06:40.400
That's really
interesting stuff.

06:42.069 --> 06:44.363
Let me take this in
and see what they think.

06:44.363 --> 06:46.198
Oh, I'll come too.
I could present.

06:46.198 --> 06:48.867
Yeah, I just...you know...
I don't know.

06:48.867 --> 06:50.202
I worry that if you came in

06:50.202 --> 06:51.995
and did this
whole presentation,

06:51.995 --> 06:55.457
would anybody know what to do
with that process-wise?

06:55.457 --> 06:57.292
You know?

06:57.292 --> 06:59.545
But don't stop
bringing me ideas.

06:59.545 --> 07:00.420
Really.

07:00.420 --> 07:01.421
Interesting stuff.

07:07.511 --> 07:09.805
[distant muffled chatter]

07:09.805 --> 07:11.348
[phone rings distantly]

07:15.310 --> 07:18.313
[phone ringing]

07:18.313 --> 07:21.316
[ambient humming]

07:21.316 --> 07:24.319
[phone continues ringing]

07:25.863 --> 07:27.656
[sighs]

07:29.408 --> 07:31.827
- [phone rings loudly]
- [receiver clatters]

07:31.827 --> 07:33.745
Geist Executive.
How can I help you?

07:34.538 --> 07:36.665
Hi.
This is Pam Bailey at the DOD.

07:36.665 --> 07:37.791
I have a situation here.

07:37.791 --> 07:38.959
It's somewhat urgent.

07:38.959 --> 07:40.419
Colin's out of the office.

07:40.419 --> 07:41.795
I know Colin's out
of the office.

07:41.795 --> 07:43.005
He just accosted my auditor

07:43.005 --> 07:44.047
in fucking Tampa.

07:44.673 --> 07:46.258
- "Accosted"?
[Pam] Yeah.

07:46.258 --> 07:48.051
Right outside
your little facility.

07:48.051 --> 07:49.553
Why?
What did he...

07:49.553 --> 07:51.221
[Pam] Audrey, I need you
to listen to me.

07:51.221 --> 07:52.139
Okay.

07:53.140 --> 07:55.350
I'm not gonna be reachable
moving forward, all right?

07:55.350 --> 07:56.643
[Temple]
I don't understand...

07:56.643 --> 07:57.603
[sharply] Listen.

07:57.603 --> 07:58.687
Me, you guys,

07:58.687 --> 08:00.606
we haven't been in touch...

08:00.606 --> 08:01.815
ever.

08:01.815 --> 08:03.400
In fact, we're not talking now.

08:03.400 --> 08:04.276
We're not?

08:04.276 --> 08:05.235
No.

08:05.235 --> 08:06.278
Okay.

08:06.361 --> 08:07.571
The complaint's been elevated.

08:07.738 --> 08:09.198
There's going to be
an investigation.

08:09.198 --> 08:10.908
- Into...
- Yep.

08:10.908 --> 08:12.743
[eerie music]

08:12.743 --> 08:14.745
Oh, my God.
What do I do?

08:14.745 --> 08:16.455
I don't know.
Get a lawyer.

08:16.455 --> 08:17.581
I'm in trouble?

08:17.581 --> 08:18.540
I don't know,

08:18.540 --> 08:19.833
but lose my number.

08:19.833 --> 08:21.627
- [dial tone]
- Wait, Pam.

08:21.627 --> 08:28.634
♪ ♪

08:29.968 --> 08:31.303
Well...

08:31.303 --> 08:33.096
- [object slams]
- I'm going to jail.

08:33.096 --> 08:34.264
[doo-wop music
playing softly]

08:34.264 --> 08:36.767
♪ And I feel so bad ♪

08:36.767 --> 08:41.897
♪ 'Cause I need someone's,
mm, heaven ♪

08:41.897 --> 08:45.150
♪ Ooh, yeah...

08:47.486 --> 08:50.072
- Why is this damp?
- Because it got wet.

08:50.072 --> 08:51.198
Why did it get wet?

08:52.074 --> 08:53.742
Is this a thought experiment?

08:53.742 --> 08:55.244
[Temple] You can use
the white ones by the shower

08:55.244 --> 08:56.411
or the green ones
in the closet.

08:56.411 --> 08:57.412
This is for decor only.

08:58.330 --> 08:59.915
"Decor only"?

08:59.915 --> 09:01.250
I thought you were going
to jail.

09:01.250 --> 09:03.377
[sighs]
This isn't a joke.

09:04.127 --> 09:06.797
The Department of Defense is
investigating my company.

09:06.797 --> 09:07.839
Why?

09:07.839 --> 09:09.132
Why do you think?

09:09.132 --> 09:11.385
♪ Hold you in my arms...

09:11.385 --> 09:12.928
- Homecoming?
- [Temple snaps her fingers]

09:12.928 --> 09:13.971
[Temple] Bingo.

09:13.971 --> 09:15.430
♪ I need you now...

09:15.430 --> 09:17.266
Are you seriously doing that
right now?

09:17.266 --> 09:18.600
[Temple] What?

09:18.600 --> 09:20.185
You just got finished
telling me

09:20.185 --> 09:21.436
that you're being investigated
for that shit,

09:21.520 --> 09:23.272
and you're slathering it
on your arm.

09:23.272 --> 09:25.065
It's topical.
It's safe.

09:25.065 --> 09:26.858
I really wish you could hear
how you sound.

09:26.858 --> 09:28.110
I do.

09:28.110 --> 09:29.820
- It calls me down, okay?
- Mm-hmm.

09:29.820 --> 09:31.446
You seem real calm.

09:31.446 --> 09:33.031
Look, if you're not going
to help...

09:33.031 --> 09:34.950
I already told you what to do.

09:34.950 --> 09:37.244
- Quit.
- It's too late for that, Alex.

09:37.244 --> 09:39.079
- I was there from the start.
[Alex] No.

09:39.079 --> 09:41.290
You don't wanna quit.
That's what's going on.

09:41.290 --> 09:44.001
You feel some sort of twisted
loyalty to this company...

09:44.001 --> 09:45.711
Yeah, okay, fine.
You're right.

09:47.254 --> 09:49.756
♪ You tried to give me ♪

09:49.756 --> 09:53.343
♪ Your love and time ♪

09:53.343 --> 09:57.389
♪ But I didn't even take you ♪

09:57.389 --> 09:59.599
♪ Take you in my arms ♪

09:59.599 --> 10:02.894
♪ So all I can do now...

10:02.894 --> 10:04.688
Who else knows
about the investigation?

10:06.273 --> 10:07.607
Right now, just me.

10:08.859 --> 10:10.110
Well, that helps.

10:10.110 --> 10:12.821
♪ I'll see you once again...

10:12.821 --> 10:14.197
[dramatic piano music]

10:14.197 --> 10:15.449
What?
What are you thinking?

10:16.325 --> 10:17.701
Colin.

10:17.701 --> 10:20.704
[Temple] What about him?
- He's a tool.

10:20.704 --> 10:22.789
Yeah, he's a jerk, but what
does that have to do with...

10:22.789 --> 10:27.044
No, he's a tool
and we can use him.

10:27.044 --> 10:28.587
This is an opportunity.

10:28.587 --> 10:30.297
♪ ♪

10:30.297 --> 10:31.757
[cork pops]

10:31.757 --> 10:33.216
[Temple]
[sighs] this is ridiculous.

10:33.216 --> 10:34.968
No it's not.

10:34.968 --> 10:37.262
He wants a meeting with Ron,
right?

10:37.262 --> 10:40.223
So you set the meeting
but you just don't tell Ron.

10:40.223 --> 10:42.726
♪ ♪

10:42.726 --> 10:45.062
[music quickens]

10:45.062 --> 10:46.313
[computer bleeps]

10:46.313 --> 10:49.149
[tense music]

10:49.149 --> 10:56.114
♪ ♪

10:56.114 --> 10:58.241
[slurps]

11:00.243 --> 11:02.579
- Good afternoon, Colin.
- Where's Ron?

11:02.579 --> 11:03.872
I'm not sure.

11:05.040 --> 11:06.958
So I just lie.

11:06.958 --> 11:08.919
[both laugh]

11:08.919 --> 11:10.629
The way you just said that
was... [chuckles]

11:10.629 --> 11:11.755
What?

11:11.755 --> 11:14.216
It was so earnest...

11:14.216 --> 11:16.426
but it was also so sexy.

11:16.426 --> 11:18.720
And yes, you are going to lie.

11:18.720 --> 11:19.930
[Colin]
Now why don't you step outside

11:19.930 --> 11:22.391
and see if you can track
Ron down?

11:22.391 --> 11:24.309
Ron's not coming, Colin.

11:24.309 --> 11:25.644
Uh...

11:25.644 --> 11:27.729
and so what are you doing here?

11:27.729 --> 11:29.773
I'm in a new role.

11:29.773 --> 11:31.066
So...

11:31.066 --> 11:32.150
say he buys it.

11:32.150 --> 11:33.735
Mm-hmm.
He will.

11:33.735 --> 11:35.320
[paper crinkling]

11:35.362 --> 11:38.573
Even then, he'll just
talk his way out of it.

11:38.573 --> 11:39.866
That's what he does.

11:39.866 --> 11:42.327
So let him talk...

11:42.327 --> 11:44.413
until he's saying
what you want.

11:44.413 --> 11:45.580
Okay, you know what?

11:45.580 --> 11:46.998
He's filing complaint.

11:46.998 --> 11:48.375
Okay?
That's just reality.

11:48.375 --> 11:50.127
So we should focus on that.

11:50.127 --> 11:51.753
Okay.
What do you suggest?

11:51.753 --> 11:53.964
What do I suggest?
We give them someone.

11:53.964 --> 11:55.132
A rogue employee.

11:55.132 --> 11:56.341
Yeah, that's right.

11:56.341 --> 11:57.551
Disobeyed protocol?

11:57.551 --> 11:58.593
Exactly.

11:59.594 --> 12:02.305
Bergman got, I don't know,
emotional, and she...

12:02.305 --> 12:03.265
Not she.

12:04.099 --> 12:05.016
What?

12:05.934 --> 12:08.061
We're not talking
about Bergman.

12:08.061 --> 12:12.065
"Including a confrontation

12:12.065 --> 12:16.653
with a Department of Defense

12:16.653 --> 12:18.905
investigator."

12:18.905 --> 12:20.490
He's never gonna sign this.

12:20.490 --> 12:23.785
He will if he sees it
as a means to an end.

12:23.785 --> 12:24.828
What end?

12:24.828 --> 12:26.079
Unemployment?

12:26.079 --> 12:28.540
♪ ♪

12:28.540 --> 12:29.583
[sighs]

12:30.959 --> 12:33.462
What's the one thing
he wants more than anything?

12:33.462 --> 12:35.839
[Temple] Mr. Geist and I
discussed all of that.

12:35.839 --> 12:38.091
If you take responsibility
for your actions,

12:38.091 --> 12:39.384
it would mean a lot to him.

12:39.384 --> 12:40.760
It could affect
your future here.

12:41.386 --> 12:42.846
You talked to...to Geist?

12:42.846 --> 12:44.681
Yes.

12:44.681 --> 12:46.683
At his farm.
Have you been?

12:47.684 --> 12:48.685
[Alex] You can do this.

12:49.352 --> 12:50.979
I believe in you.

12:50.979 --> 12:52.022
Why?

12:53.482 --> 12:55.025
I don't know.
Should I stop?

12:55.025 --> 12:57.444
♪ ♪

12:57.444 --> 12:59.029
No.

12:59.029 --> 13:06.036
♪ ♪

13:08.205 --> 13:11.208
[music heightens rapidly]

13:11.208 --> 13:18.215
♪ ♪

13:40.570 --> 13:42.864
[Leonard] So how fast
are we talking?

13:42.864 --> 13:45.242
[researcher]
The effect is immediate.

13:45.242 --> 13:47.077
[Leonard] Okay.
Let's...

13:47.077 --> 13:48.328
let's give it a try.

13:49.621 --> 13:50.789
I refuse to watch.

13:50.789 --> 13:52.374
It'll be fine.

13:52.374 --> 13:54.125
Leonard, the chemistry
is clear.

13:54.125 --> 13:56.503
Just gonna do
a little experiment.

13:56.503 --> 13:58.797
There is no reason
to abuse yourself.

13:59.923 --> 14:01.132
[yelps]

14:01.132 --> 14:02.092
Fuckin' hell!

14:02.092 --> 14:03.426
Shit, that hurt.

14:03.426 --> 14:04.636
[grunts]

14:05.804 --> 14:07.055
[quietly] Shit.

14:08.848 --> 14:10.600
[groans, exhales slowly]

14:10.600 --> 14:13.520
You are a piece of work,
you know that?

14:13.520 --> 14:15.105
God damn.

14:17.107 --> 14:18.608
[groans]

14:21.861 --> 14:22.946
Oh, damn.
That...

14:24.072 --> 14:25.907
Really took the bite out.
[laughs]

14:25.907 --> 14:28.243
[researcher] Mm-hmm.
I told you.

14:28.243 --> 14:30.120
Ah.
[inhales deeply]

14:30.120 --> 14:31.621
And the scent's not bad either.

14:32.372 --> 14:34.791
Let's talk about cultivation
next week, huh?

14:34.791 --> 14:37.002
[researcher] Yes, yes.
Cheers.

14:37.002 --> 14:39.129
- Cheers!
- [video call program bloops]

14:39.129 --> 14:40.672
[chuckles]

14:40.672 --> 14:42.757
God!
Jesus.

14:44.634 --> 14:45.594
You been here long?

14:47.053 --> 14:48.471
Sorry.
I didn't want to, uh...

14:48.471 --> 14:49.639
It's fine.

14:49.639 --> 14:50.932
What do you...what do you need?

14:50.932 --> 14:52.183
[inhales sharply]

14:55.854 --> 14:57.230
I'm Audrey Temple.

14:57.230 --> 14:58.440
Mm-hmm.

14:58.440 --> 14:59.524
I work in Redwood,

14:59.524 --> 15:01.234
or in front of it.

15:01.234 --> 15:03.153
The desk, right?

15:03.153 --> 15:04.696
- Right.
- Right.

15:11.286 --> 15:13.538
The DOD is opening
an investigation

15:13.538 --> 15:15.540
into the Homecoming program,

15:15.540 --> 15:19.377
but I have obtained
a confession from Colin Belfast

15:19.377 --> 15:21.379
accepting complete
responsibility,

15:21.379 --> 15:23.465
which I believe will help
protect the company during...

15:23.465 --> 15:24.841
Wait.
Hold up.

15:24.841 --> 15:25.842
Um...

15:27.135 --> 15:28.261
Yes?

15:29.679 --> 15:31.931
What the fuck is Homecoming?

15:31.931 --> 15:34.726
♪ ♪

15:34.726 --> 15:36.394
Okay, the first thing is...

15:36.394 --> 15:38.063
[pants]
...she's a liar.

15:39.689 --> 15:42.984
So you didn't run
the Homecoming program, huh?

15:42.984 --> 15:44.152
No!

15:44.736 --> 15:45.570
No?

15:48.698 --> 15:51.451
N...well, it...it was
a program that I worked on,

15:51.451 --> 15:54.496
certainly, but if you believe
that fucking fairy tale

15:54.496 --> 15:56.331
that she coerced me
into signing

15:56.331 --> 15:57.624
under deceptive pretenses...

15:57.666 --> 16:00.001
Now,
what part of this is false?

16:00.669 --> 16:03.505
Well, it's a matter of context,
right?

16:03.505 --> 16:06.257
I mean, any one of those...
those individual "facts"

16:06.257 --> 16:07.342
could be easily twisted...

16:07.342 --> 16:08.718
Were you dosing these guys

16:08.718 --> 16:09.886
and lying to them about it?

16:09.886 --> 16:11.262
Uh, w... [sighs]

16:13.056 --> 16:14.474
I...look, I...I don't know

16:14.474 --> 16:15.767
how detailed
we wanna get right now.

16:15.767 --> 16:17.435
That's not detail.

16:17.435 --> 16:19.312
That's simple.

16:21.481 --> 16:24.192
Okay, if I could just take
a step back for a moment.

16:24.192 --> 16:25.610
[takes deep breath]
And...and I know

16:25.610 --> 16:27.362
this goes
without saying...

16:28.488 --> 16:30.448
...but you've always been
an inspiration to me, sir.

16:31.783 --> 16:33.326
And...

16:33.326 --> 16:35.036
if I flew a little
too close to the sun...

16:35.036 --> 16:36.621
Okay.
So you did.

16:38.206 --> 16:40.458
And you, Ron?

16:40.458 --> 16:41.960
Oh, I'm just playing catch-up
here.

16:41.960 --> 16:42.794
[Colin scoffs]

16:42.794 --> 16:44.087
But I can say

16:44.170 --> 16:45.296
I'm disgusted
at what I'm hearing.

16:45.547 --> 16:47.257
Oh, you're disgusted, Ron?
Really?

16:47.257 --> 16:48.925
That's interesting, because...

16:48.925 --> 16:51.720
- Colin's your guy, right?
[Ron] He's on my team.

16:51.720 --> 16:53.763
But clearly, I've given him
way too much latitude.

16:54.472 --> 16:55.640
Right...

16:55.640 --> 16:57.475
as did I with Audrey.

16:57.475 --> 17:00.603
So what we have here
is a...a latitude problem.

17:00.603 --> 17:02.981
No, we don't.

17:02.981 --> 17:04.816
...have a latitude problem.

17:04.816 --> 17:08.194
The protocol we outlined
was based on topical use.

17:08.194 --> 17:10.447
Yeah, exactly.
Like the roller.

17:10.447 --> 17:11.865
But when you weren't getting
results,

17:11.865 --> 17:13.700
you insisted
that it be ingested.

17:13.700 --> 17:15.201
What? They were drinking it?

17:15.201 --> 17:17.954
- Actually...
- No. You, answer me.

17:20.665 --> 17:22.500
No, technically,
they were eating it.

17:22.500 --> 17:24.502
But...but they all signed
waivers.

17:24.502 --> 17:26.379
- So we're clean.
- What happened to them?

17:26.921 --> 17:27.756
To who?

17:27.756 --> 17:28.673
[sighs]

17:28.673 --> 17:29.674
The men.

17:30.717 --> 17:31.718
[clicks tongue softly]

17:31.718 --> 17:32.677
Well, different things.

17:32.677 --> 17:33.928
Ah, Jesus Christ.

17:33.928 --> 17:35.180
And you knew what he was doing.

17:35.180 --> 17:36.723
I mean, no.

17:36.723 --> 17:38.391
Y...well, yes.
At the time, you're saying?

17:38.391 --> 17:39.893
Well,
what the fuck does that mean?

17:39.893 --> 17:41.811
Uh, I'm...I'm just trying
to think of...

17:41.811 --> 17:43.104
What? Which one I wanna hear?

17:43.104 --> 17:44.731
No, no, no, no.
I'm...I wanna...

17:44.731 --> 17:46.608
I just w...I want..
I wanna build a time line.

17:46.608 --> 17:47.859
Okay.
Okay.

17:47.859 --> 17:49.569
Both of ya are fired.

17:49.569 --> 17:50.403
What?

17:51.571 --> 17:53.323
Sir?
S...oh.

17:53.323 --> 17:54.783
With all due respect,

17:54.866 --> 17:56.493
we've got this investigation
bearing down.

17:56.493 --> 17:57.535
I...I think we should be

17:57.535 --> 17:59.245
circling the wagons, sir.

18:00.455 --> 18:02.582
Okay, who's gonna manage this
day to day?

18:02.582 --> 18:05.168
[Ron] This is
a federal investigation.

18:07.378 --> 18:08.296
I will.

18:11.174 --> 18:12.383
Yeah, she will.

18:15.553 --> 18:17.096
I'm not trying
to be an asshole, here,

18:17.096 --> 18:18.515
but Audrey answers the phones.

18:18.515 --> 18:19.724
Hey, we tried with you clowns,

18:19.724 --> 18:21.142
and now we're all covered
in shit.

18:21.142 --> 18:22.477
I don't think she can
do any worse.

18:24.062 --> 18:25.647
Hey, Hector.

18:25.647 --> 18:27.232
Hey.

18:27.232 --> 18:28.691
We gotta plant a bunch more
of those gourds,

18:28.691 --> 18:30.276
okay, buddy?

18:30.276 --> 18:32.070
We gotta use the hand tools.
So...

18:32.654 --> 18:33.947
No, I know it takes longer.

18:33.947 --> 18:35.114
That's why we gotta get movin'.

18:35.698 --> 18:37.659
So you're, like, a...

18:37.659 --> 18:38.618
good person?

18:40.328 --> 18:41.454
Is that the idea?

18:43.915 --> 18:45.041
Your shoe's untied.

18:46.793 --> 18:49.796
[dramatic music]

18:49.796 --> 18:54.717
♪ ♪

18:54.717 --> 18:55.844
Uh-huh.

18:56.845 --> 18:58.513
So what exactly
are they claiming?

18:58.513 --> 19:03.142
♪ ♪

19:03.142 --> 19:04.686
No.
Yeah.

19:04.686 --> 19:06.354
I've...I've...
I've dealt with that before.

19:07.355 --> 19:08.439
It's not a problem.

19:08.439 --> 19:13.486
♪ ♪

19:13.486 --> 19:16.364
So basically,
my role is prophylactic.

19:16.364 --> 19:19.826
I go in before litigation,
before things get messy,

19:19.826 --> 19:21.828
and I make contact
with the complainant

19:21.828 --> 19:23.496
and find an off-ramp for them.

19:23.496 --> 19:26.082
I'd help them see that
that is their best option.

19:26.082 --> 19:27.500
♪ ♪

19:27.500 --> 19:28.918
Yeah.

19:28.918 --> 19:31.212
Uh, copyright,
wrongful termination,

19:31.212 --> 19:34.340
personal injury.
You know, just to name a few.

19:34.340 --> 19:36.509
Yes, any type
of negative exposure,

19:36.509 --> 19:38.720
I can limit that.

19:38.720 --> 19:41.723
♪ ♪

19:41.723 --> 19:44.392
Well, I use a number
of...of different approaches.

19:44.392 --> 19:47.937
♪ ♪

19:47.937 --> 19:48.980
[car door slams shut]

19:48.980 --> 19:51.691
♪ ♪

19:51.691 --> 19:54.277
Hey, do you mind
if I give you a call back?

19:54.277 --> 19:55.612
Okay. Talk soon.

19:55.612 --> 19:57.488
[door clicks open]

19:57.488 --> 19:58.489
[door clicks shut]

19:58.489 --> 20:00.408
So...

20:00.408 --> 20:01.492
how did it go?

20:02.952 --> 20:03.870
Are you the new Colin?

20:05.997 --> 20:07.874
I think I'm the new Ron.

20:08.958 --> 20:10.001
Yeah, you are.

20:11.586 --> 20:13.087
I was nervous at first,

20:13.087 --> 20:15.465
but Colin was
just so desperate.

20:15.465 --> 20:17.091
And he was like,
"You can't do this,"

20:17.091 --> 20:18.593
and "I'm a problem solver."

20:18.593 --> 20:19.802
[chuckling]
And I was like,

20:19.802 --> 20:21.346
"You were a problem solver,

20:21.346 --> 20:23.139
but now you are a problem."

20:23.139 --> 20:24.682
Fuck, I wish
you would've filmed it.

20:24.682 --> 20:27.602
And Leonard,
he just listened to me.

20:27.602 --> 20:29.312
Right away he believed me.

20:29.312 --> 20:32.482
And now he wants me
to deal with the DOD.

20:34.150 --> 20:36.527
Can I do that?
I mean, I can't do that.

20:36.527 --> 20:38.655
Yes, you can.

20:38.655 --> 20:40.281
Just give them the confession.

20:40.281 --> 20:41.783
They just wanna
hold someone responsible.

20:41.783 --> 20:43.785
Colin is responsible.
It's that simple.

20:43.785 --> 20:46.245
It's a friggin'
federal investigation.

20:46.245 --> 20:47.997
I can't just walk in there
and...

20:47.997 --> 20:49.332
Look at me.

20:49.332 --> 20:50.833
You can do this.

20:50.833 --> 20:52.293
You've basically
already done it.

20:54.879 --> 20:56.005
[teeth click together]

20:56.005 --> 20:57.215
- [Alex grunts]
- Oh.

20:57.215 --> 20:58.758
Oh, my God.

20:58.758 --> 21:00.009
Babe, it's okay.

21:00.009 --> 21:02.261
- Oh, my God.
[Alex] It's fine.

21:02.261 --> 21:03.346
[foreboding music]

21:03.346 --> 21:04.472
No, you need to...

21:04.472 --> 21:06.432
[ice clanging]

21:06.432 --> 21:07.475
God.

21:07.475 --> 21:10.144
♪ ♪

21:10.144 --> 21:11.521
Here.

21:11.521 --> 21:12.814
Ice it before it swells.

21:12.814 --> 21:17.610
♪ ♪

21:17.610 --> 21:19.779
Those are for decor only, babe.

21:19.779 --> 21:26.786
♪ ♪

21:37.922 --> 21:39.924
[music swells]

21:39.924 --> 21:43.136
- [music stops abruptly]
- [birds chirping]

21:43.136 --> 21:45.805
